be a reference to {{wp|rocket launcher}}s, with its tree-like tail also resembling a rocket.\n\n====Name origin====\nSceptile may be a combination of \'\'{{wp|reptile}}\'\' and \'\'{{wp|Sceptridium}}\'\' (referring to its fern-like tail) or \'\'{{wp|sectility|sectile}}\'\' (referring to the sharp blades growing on its body). It may also derive from \'\'{{wp|sceptre|scepter}}\'\' (from its title as "King of the Forest") or \'\'{{wp|scissors}}\'\' (referring to the blades on its wrists).\n\nJukain may derive from 樹海 \'\'jukai\'\' (abundant leafage).\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Grass|type2=Grass\n|ja=ジュカイン \'\'Jukain\'\'|jameaning=From {{tt|樹海 \'\'jukai\'\'|dense woodland}}\n|fr=Jungko|frmeaning=From \'\'jungle\'\' and \'\'gecko\'\'\n|es=Sceptile|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Gewaldro|demeaning=From \'\'{{tt|Gewalt|force or power}}\'\', \'\'{{tt|Wald|forest}}\'\', and \'\'{{tt|drohen|to threaten}}\'\'\n|it=Sceptile|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=나무킹 \'\'Namuking\'\'|komeaning=From {{tt|나무 \'\'namu\'\'|tree}} and \'\'king\'\'\n|zh_yue=蜥蜴王 \'\'Sīkyihkwòhng\'\'|zh_yuemeaning=Literally "Lizard king"\n|zh_cmn=蜥蜴王 \'\'Xīyìwáng\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=Literally "Lizard king"\n|hi=स्केप्टइल \'\'Sceptile\'\'|himeaning=Transcription of English name\n|ru=Септайл \'\'Septayl\'\'|rumeaning=Transcription of English name\n}}\n<br clear="left">\n\n==Related articles==\n* [[Ash\'s Sceptile]]\n* [[Sawyer\'s Sceptile]]\n* [[Emerald\'s Sceptile]]\n* [[Starter Pokémon]]\n\n==Notes==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n\n{{-}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Grass}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Grass|prevnum=253|prev=Grovyle|nextnum=255|next=Torchic}}\n|}\n{{Project Pokédex notice}}\n\n[[de:Gewaldro]]\n[[es:Sceptile]]\n[[fr:Jungko]]\n[[it:Sceptile]]\n[[ja:ジュカイン]]\n[[zh:蜥蜴王]]'}